      • newServerside

        public GClient newServerside(java.nio.channels.AsynchronousSocketChannel socketChannel,
                             PacketProcessor packetProcessor,
                             java.util.UUID sessionUUID,
                             Pool<com.github.yona168.giraffe.net.packet.ReceivablePacket> pool)

        Creates a class GClient from a given AsynchronousSocketChannel that will not connect on enable. It also has a given sessionUUID.

        Parameters:
        socketChannel - The already-connected AsynchronousSocketChannel to use.
        packetProcessor - The interface PacketProcessor to use.
        sessionUUID - The UUID to set the client's Client.getSessionUUID to
        pool - The interface Pool to get empty packets from, defaulting to class ByteBufferReceivablePacketPool
        Returns:
        A class GClient to wrap the given channel.
        See Also:
        class GClient, AsynchronousSocketChannel

      • newClientside

        public GClient newClientside(java.net.SocketAddress address,
                             long timeoutMillis,
                             PacketProcessor packetProcessor,
                             Pool<com.github.yona168.giraffe.net.packet.ReceivablePacket> pool)

        Creates a class GClient that opens a new AsynchronousSocketChannel and connects it to the address when it enables.

        Parameters:
        address - The SocketAddress to connect to on enable.
        packetProcessor - The interface PacketProcessor to use, defaulting to CustomContextPacketProcessor.Companion.defaultDispatch
        timeoutMillis - How long the client will wait to finish connecting before giving up (in milliseconds), defaulting to 1000.
        pool - The pool to get empty packets from, defaulting to a class ByteBufferReceivablePacketPool.
        Returns:
        A class GClient that, when enabled, attempts to connect to a server specified by the address.
        See Also:
        class GClient, AsynchronousSocketChannel
